                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout rend="arris_up">The stone features a roman-letter inscription reading vertically downwards in two lines, and is described as being lightly <rs type="execution" key="incised" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1.html">incised.</rs> The roman-letter inscription takes up much of the central third of the stone face, though is positioned to the right of centre. <q>The ogam inscription is incised on the left angle (A/D) reading upwards</q> (Edwards 2007, 331).</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><q>The [roman-letter] inscription is in capitals. In line 1 the A's have angle-bars; G is sickle-shaped; the L's have sloping horizontals and the final I of <hi rend="italic">Andagelli</hi> is horizontal. In line 2 FI are conjoined with a small I; AV are ligatured and the final I is horizontal</q> (Edwards 2007, 331).
                                <height></height>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
