        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve">
                <div type="textpart" n="1" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name nymRef="#ANDEGELLAS">&#x1690;&#x1685;&#x1687;&#x1690;&#x168C;&#x1693;&#x1682;&#x1682;&#x1694;</name><w lemma="#MAQQAS" type="patronym" corresp="http://www.dil.ie/31166">&#x168B;&#x1690;&#x1689;&#x1692;</w><name nymRef="#CAVETAS">&#x1689;&#x1690;&#x1683;&#x1693;&#x1688;&#x1694;</name></persName>
                </ab>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam">
                <div type="textpart" n="1">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up" break="no"/><persName><name nymRef="#ANDEGELLAS">ANDAGELLI</name><w lemma="#MAQQAS" type="patronym" corresp="http://www.dil.ie/31166">MACU</w><name nymRef="#CAVETAS">CAVETI</name></persName>
                    </ab>
                </div>
               </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="roman" xml:space="preserve">
                    <div type="textpart" n="2" xml:lang="pgl-Latn">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:down"/><persName><name nymRef="#ANDEGELLAS">ANDAGELL<hi rend="inverted">I</hi></name><w>IACIT</w>
                    <lb n="2" style="text-direction:down"/><w><hi rend="ligature">FI</hi>LI</w><name nymRef="#CAVETAS">C<hi rend="ligature">AV</hi>ET<hi rend="inverted">I</hi></name></persName>
                </ab>
               </div>
            </div>            
            <div type="apparatus">
                <p></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <div type="textpart" n="1">
                    <p><title>Ogham</title>: 'of <foreign xml:lang="pgl">Andagellus</foreign> son of <foreign xml:lang="pgl">Cavetus</foreign>'</p>
                </div>
               </div>
              <div type="textpart" n="2">
                  <p><title>Latin</title>: 'of <foreign xml:lang="pgl">Andagellus</foreign>, (here) he lies, son of <foreign xml:lang="pgl">Cavetus</foreign>'</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                        <p><q>Although the last two letters are damaged, the ogam inscription may be reconstructed with certainty. It mirrors the Latin but without <hi rend="italic">iacit</hi>. MACU is written instead of the usual <q>maqi</q>... ANDAGELLI... is probably not British but a preform of the poorly attested OI <hi rend="italic">Indgall</hi>, 'very yellow'... The initial A- has been regarded as British or British-influenced, but could be an archaic Irish feature, since OI <hi rend="italic">Ind-</hi> developed from <hi rend="italic">*Ande-</hi>. The name can alternatively be segmented AN-DAG-ELLI, 'little bad one'</q> (Edwards 2007, 331).</p>
                        <p>The roman-letter inscription <q>consists of the 'X son of Y' formula in the genitive case with the addition of <hi rend="italic">iacit</hi>. The incorporation of the abbreviated <hi rend="italic">hic iacit</hi> formula indicates that the inscription is Christian</q> (Edwards 2007, 331).</p>
                    </div>
